<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-01-09</DATELINE><TITLE>Developing vaccines to counter bioterrorist threats</TITLE><BODY>Large and innovative research programs are underway to define the immune parameters for vaccines against a wide array of pathogens considered to represent a potential bioterrorist threat. However, the development and utilization of such vaccines presents a number of predicaments that have not previously been addressed by the field of vaccinology.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>